	(34,'2016-12-14 17:16:54','2016-12-14 17:00:42','science','psychology','philosophy','[]',165,'krnel','Why did monogamy evolve?  Science has some clues!','31.493 SBD',4,'### Continuing from the [previous post](https://steemit.com/news/@krnel/monogamy-is-why-humans-don-t-have-literal-penis-bone-r-s-anymore) on monogamy, is why are we monogamous? \n\n### Why do we prefer this in general?\n\n### Is it not based on valid objective reasoning?\n\nOne of the researchers from the work on the baculum, Dr. Kit Opie, spoke for an article earlier this year, this time on the above question of monogamy. The previous post dealt with how our mammalian ancestor had penis bones in some male species, and some still do. This was tied into polygamy and the intrasexual competition and postcopulatory sexual competition for the \"seed\" to take \"root\" inside the female.\n\n<center><h1>Evolution of Monogamy<img src=\"http://www.steemimg.com/images/2016/12/14/monogamy09b68.jpg\" alt=\"monogamy09b68.jpg\" border=\"0\"><br/></h1><em><a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/79992579@N07/8472452910\">source</a></em></center>\n\nModern monogamy isn\'t wholly a human creation, we just advanced it more through socialization and cooperation that enables stronger bonds, trust, loyalty and faith. According to Opie, earlier primates, as early as 75 million years ago, had adults living mostly in isolation and coming together to copulate for that biological reason. They were driven to reproduce from the basic bio-natural subconscious motivation so survive as a species that is favored through a pleasurable experience. Any mate would suffice, as long as the urge and desires were being fulfilled. This is a basic polygamy of sexual behavior. If it was like Kevin Spacey described in it [K-PAX](http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0272152/), sex would not be something fun at all.\n\nThen, monogamy evolved more as a result of more socialization to live closer together in groups. Other primates like bonobos and chimps still have that polygamous behavior, whereas humans have evolved in the other direction towards more monogamy.\n\nWhy? Theories revolve around the preservation of an individuals health, their offspring, and their wealth through marriage contracts.\n\n---\n<center><h2>Sexually Transmitted Diseases</h2></center>\n\n<div class=\"pull-left\"><center><img src=\"http://www.steemimg.com/images/2016/12/14/no_std8df46.jpg\" alt=\"no_std8df46.jpg\" border=\"0\"><br/><em><a href=\"http://escambia.floridahealth.gov/programs-and-services/clinical-and-nutrition-services/std/index.html\">source</a></em></center></div>\n\nAnother reason to lead us back to monogamy, not not wide ranging sexual behavior of multiple partners are the known health issues,like STDs. Chris Bauch, from the University of Waterloo, did a [study on diseases and sexual behavior](www.nature.com/ncomms/2016/160412/ncomms11219/full/ncomms11219.html) to conclude health and social pressures for monogamous living. As I said in my previous post, our trust and loyalty in others is optimized through sexual faith in another, which is part of healthy sexual behavior.\n\nThis is a natural law causal effect. Something wrong is happening, and it needs to change. A behavior will be restricted, and censored from happening or being publicly accepted. People willingly change through recognizing truth, or not, and are force by social pressure, shunning, ostrasization, etc., to change their behavior. Social norms develop in conjunction with environmental causal realities. \n\nThe larger a population gets, the more options for multiple partners exist, and an exponential increase in risk of sexual transmissions exists. In smaller groups, like tribal clans of 30 or so people, there were less people, and less partners for multiple sexual transmission of diseases. In large societies where fertility capacity is affected by diseases like syphilis, chlamydia and gonorrhea, monogamy affords an advantage to men who want to produce offspring by allowing them to find someone health, and themselves remain healthy to spear their seed.\n\nAdditionally, this close relationship fosters an environment to raise children and ensure their success in society, and further propagate your genetic lineage into the future ensuring your own survival in part, and that of humanities. Polygamy would then result in an SDT punishment, and not be desired. But this is also only part of the shift to monogamy.\n\n---\n<center><h2>Agriculture, Family, Marriage, Property and Health<br/><img src=\"http://www.steemimg.com/images/2016/12/14/stick-family-1449578741cAV4f0f7.jpg\" alt=\"stick-family-1449578741cAV4f0f7.jpg\" border=\"0\"></h2><em><a href=\"http://www.publicdomainpictures.net/hledej.php?hleda=family\">source</a></em></center>\n\nThere are additional social factors influencing our evolution towards monogamy. Agriculture and farming also promote monogamy, because we accumulate wealth that ensures our own survival, and that our of children and our future descendants. Marriage, was how we locked in our property to be inherited by our family when we died. It stayed in the family, int he genetic pool, in the bloodline, in the clan we can trust. This level of trust is less developed when you degrade the sexual trust through polygamous promiscuity.\n\nEven before that, to ensure our the male\'s seed survived, if they only drank the milk and ran away from the cow after (to borrow an analogy) they still would want to protect their offspring from being murdered. You may say, sure that\'s obvious in a way, but also ask, why would they be in danger of being murdered? \n\nWell, as I am constantly emphasizing, their is a deep lower consciousness carnal lustful desire for sexual gratification through an overall pleasure trap drive we have at a subconscious bio-natural level that drives us to procreate and survive as a species. All animals have this basic drive. Living in this lower consciousness modality, is not aspiring towards evolving consciousness and higher ideals and betterment to improve our lives or the lives of everyone in general. This lower consciousness drive for sexual pleasure and gratification, is what drives much immoral behavior, like pedophilia and rape. \n\nNow that this is understood, you can maybe see where this is going in terms of needing to protect your child from being murdered in a sexually competitive promiscuous polygamous \"society\"? Other males, want sex, want to fuck, and will murder your child to get the woman.\n\n#### Infanticide is a real motivator towards monogamy! Pairing up with the partner makes for a better chance of ensuring the child lives.\n\nThe male driven by base desires with no concern for others, will rape the female after murdering the child she was taking care of. Rape was a big part of sexual behavior when being driven by lust and carnal motivations to get that itch out and spread the seed. Earlier humans, and other primates engage in infanticide to get their penis into a vagina. \"Feeling-good\" is what drives them, not matter the harm they do. \n\nThis is the drive many humans still have to this day: they are living in low base consciousness, being drive by basic bio-natural desires, and not being in control through higher order thought and rationality of their behavior. This is to operate like an \"animal\", nonhuman animal, because of the lack of higher order consciousness and thinking that humans posses. It\'s all lower consciousness drives for behavior in life. \n\nEvolving our capacity for thought, understanding consciousness, psychology, biology, will allow one to reflect, analyze and contemplate upon how much lower base consciousness pleasure gratification is motivating much of human behavior to this day. We can change, but only if we understand what we are doing. I did.\n\n---\n<center><h2>Brain Size</h2></center>\n\n<div class=\"pull-right\"><center><img src=\"http://www.steemimg.com/images/2016/12/14/350px-ComparitiveBrainSize3f4b6.jpg\" alt=\"350px-ComparitiveBrainSize3f4b6.jpg\" border=\"0\"><br/><em><a href=\"http://en.citizendium.org/wiki/Brain_size\">source</a></em></center></div>\n\nAnother evolutionary pressure was from our growing brain size to accommodate greater information and interaction from primates living closer in groups. Infants required more time to develop after birth, which required more motherly care, attention and lactation. Females were less available for mating after giving birth.\n\nAll of these factors come together to shape the development of our mostly monogamous human way of life. It was all prompted by natural causal realities of evolving into a more social and caring species. Most nonhuman mothers don\'t care for their infants nearly as long as humans do, even by comparative assessment through ratios. \n\nWe don\'t have time machines, only ideas and theories based on the evidence we have now, but it sure makes a lot of logical sense to me when I put the pieces together with my own understanding.\n\n---\n### Closing Remarks\n\nEvolution of brains and consciousness required more care, trust, loyalty and faith in each other on the part of the species as they progress. Monogamy is a positive evolution of recognizing erroneous behavioral patterns. It moved us towards less of a focus on sexual desires, gratification and the pleasure trap, where we shifted our consciousness towards higher minded ideals and works to better ourselves. Greater care, love, trust, loyalty and faith in a partner is tied to sexual behavior, whether you like it or not.\n\nI am not religious, but I really do understand why they have certain codes of conduct, despite religions not properly explaining the biological or psychological reasons for them to be right and adopted. Many people believe, erroneously, that non-monogamy is our \"human nature\". No, it\'s part of being human since we are animals and still have the lower reptilian R-Complex base-brain instinctual bio-nature unconscious involuntary