ds greater fidelity, care, trust and loyalty for stronger family units and survival through deeper quality values for living and cooperative survival.\n\nI went to google images to search for monogamy, and there is such a drive from pleasure in the collective consciousness of many people these days that 1/2 of the images denigrate monogamy in favor of promoting polygamy in our post-modern devalued ill society that is degenerating down the crapper. Our technological evolution is blinding us to catch up with evolution in consciousness. Analysis of behavior in light of new technological integration into our lives, is not being done with respect to a historical, evolutionary or psychological analysis.\n\n## Never underestimate the power of denial.\n\nLooking in the mirror at our behavior is really hard for the unexamined to do. It\'s a process that needs to be worked on and developed through learning about psychology, biology, consciousness, philosophy, morality, etc. Most people don\'t want to do the work it takes to develop and evolve their consciousness. Most are too busy chasing pleasure, gratification, enjoyment, fun, activities, etc. to bother with inner-development. Then you begin to see the detrimental effect that living by a focus and drive on pleasure has for our own lives, and for the progress of humanity as a whole.\n\nThere are reasons why we progressed towards more monogamy as we evolved socially, psychologically and physically. And it\'s a good thing.\n\n---\n#### Thank you for your time and attention! I appreciate the knowledge reaching more people. Take care. Peace.\n\n###### *This post is over my 4 post daily \"limit\", I\'ll take less rewards, just getting the info out ;)*\n\n---\nReferences:\n- [Why did we become monogamous?](http://www.cnn.com/2016/05/17/health/sti-infanticide-human-monogamy/)\n- [Disease dynamics and costly punishment can foster socially imposed monogamy](http://www.nature.com/articles/ncomms11219)\n\n---\n##### If you appreciate and value the content, please consider: \n<center>Upvoting, Sharing, and Resteeming below.</center>\n\n[![Follow](https://www.steemimg.com/images/2016/08/30/follow2be5e.png)](https://steemit.com/@krnel) me for more content to come!\n\n---\n@krnel\n2016-12-14, 12pm','{\"tags\":[\"monogamy\",\"science\",\"psychology\",\"philosophy\"],\"users\":[\"krnel\"],\"image\":[\"http://www.steemimg.com/images/2016/12/14/monogamy09b68.jpg\",\"http://www.steemimg.com/images/2016/12/14/no_std8df46.jpg\",\"http://www.steemimg.com/images/2016/12/14/stick-family-1449578741cAV4f0f7.jpg\",\"http://www.steemimg.com/images/2016/12/14/350px-ComparitiveBrainSize3f4b6.jpg\",\"https://www.steemimg.com/images/2016/08/30/follow2be5e.png\"],\"links\":[\"https://steemit.com/news/@krnel/monogamy-is-why-humans-don-t-have-literal-penis-bone-r-s-anymore\",\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/79992579@N07/8472452910\",\"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0272152/\",\"http://escambia.floridahealth.gov/programs-and-services/clinical-and-nutrition-services/std/index.html\",\"www.nature.com/ncomms/2016/160412/ncomms11219/full/ncomms11219.html\",\"http://www.publicdomainpictures.net/hledej.php?hleda=family\",\"http://en.citizendium.org/wiki/Brain_size\",\"http://www.cnn.com/2016/05/17/health/sti-infanticide-human-monogamy/\",\"http://www.nature.com/articles/ncomms11219\",\"https://steemit.com/@krnel\"],\"app\":\"steemit/0.1\",\"format\":\"markdown\"}','steem','[\"kafkanarchy84\",\"fyrstikken\",\"runridefly\",\"craig-grant\",\"yuliana\",\"arama\",\"blueorgy\",\"enki\",\"xeldal\",\"baerdric\",\"oldtimer\",\"mrs.agsexplorer\",\"sunscape\",\"steem-meme\",\"hilarski\",\"dragonslayer109\",\"dirkzett\",\"angel76\",\"sethlinson\",\"febird\",\"uri-bruck\",\"jwaser\",\"mark-waser\",\"morgan.waser\",\"ethical-ai\",\"herpetologyguy\",\"bwaser\",\"strong-ai\",\"digital-wisdom\",\"davidjkelley\",\"technoprogressiv\",\"ellepdub\",\"adelja\",\"qubes\",\"sponge-bob\",\"brains\",\"tommyhansen\",\"portuguesinha\",\"lloyddavis\",\"heroic1