	(35,'2016-12-14 17:02:24','2016-12-14 17:02:24','story','travel','til','life',10,'scan0017','Quento and Craiggles go traveling #1','13.165 SBD',2,'Think back over your life...  Have you ever been to New Orleans?  Have you experienced the sights, sounds, the VIBE of the French Quarter?  We did, and it was AMAZING.  The night began as it should:  With an authentic, delicious, very memorable dinner at a restaurant on Bourbon Street.\n[![IMG_1265.jpg](https://s23.postimg.org/6r2zbd1d7/IMG_1265.jpg)](https://postimg.org/image/j5prbosvb/)\nYou can feel the energy of Bourbon Street live and direct from the front door; stepping inside, the frequency shifts - to a tighter, more intimate  vivacity.\n[![IMG_1266.jpg](https://s30.postimg.org/soqebz5mp/IMG_1266.jpg)](https://postimg.org/image/96vqw18ot/)\nFood selection was out of control and made us wish our capacity to consume was larger than what we came in with...\n[![IMG_1257.jpg](https://s24.postimg.org/y3p6z7rnp/IMG_1257.jpg)](https://postimg.org/image/885gg0ptt/)\nQuento and I started with the alligator\n[![IMG_1258.jpg](https://s27.postimg.org/7nxble2vn/IMG_1258.jpg)](https://postimg.org/image/sxkxw8j67/)\nIf you\'re wondering, yes!  It did taste a bit like chicken :)\nNext came oysters...  Which tasted nothing at all like chicken.\n[![IMG_1260.jpg](https://s27.postimg.org/ip1ua2s83/IMG_1260.jpg)](https://postimg.org/image/9h9ltdl5r/)\nThen the main course:\n[![IMG_1261.jpg](https://s23.postimg.org/8he3wcwij/IMG_1261.jpg)](https://postimg.org/image/4xs66jtsn/)\nA delicious shrimp gumbo concoction.\nFantastic start to the night!\nIf you ever find yourself along this amazing stretch of American history, mythology, and legend that is Bourbon Street, I recommend this restaurant:  fantastic service, fair prices, and heavenly food!\n[![IMG_1263.jpg](https://s29.postimg.org/i6vzckb4n/IMG_1263.jpg)](https://postimg.org/image/reo7t9i6r/)','{\"tags\":[\"food\",\"story\",\"travel\",\"til\",\"life\"],\"image\":[\"https://s23.posti