	(54,'2016-12-14 17:19:24','2016-12-14 14:28:27','technology','medicine','future','[]',1,'alcibiades','The Future of Humankind - Changes We May Experience #1','17.957 SBD',0,'![](https://newevolutiondesigns.com/images/freebies/futuristic-city-wallpaper-26.jpg)\n\nUp until this point, many predictions of scientists and sci-fi writers have already become a reality, but what does the future bring? In hundred years, how would our world look like? Are we still driving cars and waiting in traffic? Are computers all over our world? Do we keep our heads in the jars? What animals have been extinct? Will there be a universal cure for all diseases?\n\nIs there a possibility that we\'ll have to adapt for a life under water, in an ice age or in space? What can cause a Utopian outcome?\n\nWe could imagine so many different things, but let\'s have \'known\' laws of physics and tested prototypes as guidelines for our assumptions.\n***I\'ll make this into a multiple-part series since there is so many possible scenarios and visions to discuss.***\n\nSo, it\'s the year 2116. Let\'s imagine how could our modern life look like. \n\n***\n\n# Our bodies and our environment will be able to self-reconfigure\n\n![](https://www.youthreporter.eu/cache/wfimage/4952725a7100b5e273dd2080115f47f0.jpg)\n\nIn the past, robots had specific shapes, sizes and usage based on purpose they are built for. Whether they are used for cleaning the house or for production in car industry, robots we know are rigid and unable to change form (with exception of that T1000 terminator).\n\nBut let\'s imagine for a second that we can combine several of these robots into a small \"team\" that can transform itself whenever in need for a different task. For example, it may become a worm-like entity to crawl through a small hole, then create some sort of wheel to roll down the descent and finally transform into a spider-like creature to cross bumpy terrain.\n\nThis is called self-reconfiguring modular robotic system. These tiny modules can have censors, electronics, processors, memory and \'actuators\', components responsible for mechanism control. Modules have the ability to appear or disappear, connect or disconnect from each other and control their relation towards environment.\n\nWith their ability to adjust to different forms, they have big advantage compared to classical robots. Now imagine if these modular robots are microscopic, constructed in molecular nanotechnology with \"intelligent\" polymorphic substances. They would have 8 arms pointing in all directions to connect with neighbors, share energy and information.\n\n![](https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d4/Foglet.jpg/220px-Foglet.jpg)\n\nThis is known as [utility fog](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Utility_fog), and these nanobots are called \"foglets\". They could take the shape of virtually anything, so your nightstand can transform into a sofa in the morning and your house could disassemble to make room for a swimming pool.\n\nAnother huge application of the nanobots will be in the human body itself. They will be injected all over our bodies to enhance our abilities, upgrade lack of our immune system and replace damaged parts like we do on automobiles today. In a futuristic ideology known as [transhumanism](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transhumanism), we will no longer be limited by our physiology, but become the biological machines on the inside.\n\n***\n\n# Augmented reality will be a part of everyday life\n\n![](http://www.pcrevue.sk/files/photo/2016-02/10061/6fd574/Trendy2.png)\n\nWhen internet becomes available through contact lenses, we\'ll be able to overlay our physical perception with virtual content. Virtual objects will become part of our physical reality, that way creating a compelling experience.\n\nUsing this extended reality we will have all the information we need in a blink of an eye. You won\'t have to go to the store to try the new season\'s clothing or to see how some piece of furniture will look like in your living room. Teachers, speakers, historians will have all the maps, references and materials instantly. Actors will have their scripts. Tourists all the necessary guides. \n\nWhen looking for new piece of electronic, simply pointing at the device will pull all the necessary information, prices and reviews. \n\nGetting to know a person might not be that exciting since you\'ll have their entire biography available, and it\'s probably going to be some sort of scoring system to check for personality match. \n\nMuch of this is already starting to happen with companies like Google and [Ikea](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xC6t2eEPkPc). Smartphones and tablet computer possess elements like camera, gps, compass and accelerator which makes them excellent medium for augmented reality testing. [Head-mounted displays](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Head-mounted_display), helmet-like devices that, when placed on a forehead, show the elements of both physical and virtual reality to a person. Even though there are some challenges and privacy issues, this concept is only going to expand in the future.\n\n***\n*Images [1](http://www.wallpaperup.com/658128/sci-fi_futuristic_city_cities_art_artwork.html), [2](https://flipboard.com/@debra47/futuristic-living-k48q13h8z), [3](wikimedia.org), [4](http://www.pcworld.com/article/2060535/googles-augmented-reality-game-ingress-opens-to-everyone.html)*\n\n***\n\n### *<center>Hope you like this first part! If you do, don\'t forget to upvote, comment and resteem it. Also make sure to follow @alcibiades to stay updated about future posts.</center>*\n\n<center>[![](http://i.imgsafe.org/c703ef0d77.png)](https://steemit.com/@alcibiades)</center>','{\"tags\":[\"science\",\"technology\",\"medicine\",\"future\"],\"users\":[\"alcibiades\"],\"image\":[\"https://newevolutiondesigns.com/images/freebies/futuristic-city-wallpaper-26.jpg\",\"https://www.youthreporter.eu/cache/wfimage/4952725a7100b5e273dd2080115f47f0.jpg\",\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d4/Foglet.jpg/220px-Foglet.jpg\",\"http://www.pcrevue.sk/files/photo/2016-02/10061/6fd574/Trendy2.png\",\"http://i.imgsafe.org/c703ef0d77.png\"],\"links\":[\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Utility_fog\",\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transhumanism\",\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xC6t2eEPkPc\",\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Head-mounted_display\",\"http://www.wallpaperup.com/658128/sci-fi_futuristic_city_cities_art_artwork.html\",\"https://flipboard.com/@debra47/futuristic-living-k48q13h8z\",\"wikimedia.org\",\"http://www.pcworld.com/article/2060535/googles-augmented-reality-game-ingress-opens-to-everyone.html\",\"https://steemit.com/@alcibiades\"],\"app\":\"steemit/0.1\",\"format\":\"markdown\"}','steem','[\"barrydutton\"]','the-future-of-humankind-changes-we-may-experience-1','SBD','science'),
	(55,'2016-12-14 17:23:42','2016-12-14 17:23:42','success','growth','career','millennial',5,'portrayt','Why You Should Be Seeking Mastery & Not To Be Promoted','0.085 SBD',0,'The markets have always responded one thing, no matter what the economic situation. Industries have always paid for people who can provide value. Value comes in many forms, but ultimately a valuable person is one that enables people and organisations to get to their desired state. People are always seeking to be enriched and organisations are always seeking to have a competitive advantage, dominate their markets and ultimately secure profit. If you have a distinct set of skills or expertise that enable people and/or organisations to reach their desired state, goals or targets then you will always be in demand - you will be a value provider.\n\nBecoming a value provider means being the best at what you do and the only way to be the best at what you do is to have an incredible sense of self-awareness and to know yourself inside and out. Most of us never seek mastery in our personal or professional lives because we do not look within. We are distracted by little boxes in the form of TV’s, Phones, Tablets and Computers and the average attention span of the modern human is just eight seconds.\n\nIn the digital age we have never been so insecure, we are constantly seeking validation in the form of ‘likes’, ‘hearts’, shares and re-tweets. This insecurity and need for constant validation is ingrained within our professional lives. We tick boxes in order to secure promotions instead of mastering our craft in order achieve notoriety.\n\nHere\'s three reasons of why you should be seeking mastery and not to be promoted:\n\nYou Don’t Pigeonhole Yourself\n\nWe are living in an age of being niche in your focus but diverse and agile in your skills. This means that mastery requires constantly bettering yourself, constant development, it means always seeking to discover new and better ways of doing things. Many promotions lead down a certain track, these are the tracks that many others have followed previously. Mastery means bettering what others have done and changing the status quo. Mastery mean you achieve more than others have done in those same roles.\n\nAll Areas Of Your Life Flourish\n\nMastery is in many ways an ethos, it is a way of living your life. Mastery is not specific to our professional aspirations nor is it specific to our personal life-goals. Someone who is seeking mastery is fundamentally seeking to become the best possible version of themselves, the best mother/father, the best wife/husband, the best friend, the best volunteer, the best employee, the best daughter/son and this requires that we give every person and every activity 100% of our commitment and attention. A rising tide raises all ships, in other words, when your begin your journey of self mastery; you will find that you will be seeking to enhance every area of your life.\n\nYou will be happier, healthier and more confident\n\nHave you ever noticed how successful people walk, talk and act? They have a certain energy about them, right? This is because when we are developing as individuals, when our lives are expanding, when our skills are being perfected and our expertise is deepening we are happier and it has been proven that happier people live healthier lives. Knowledge is ultimately the key to an expansive life, when you have a deep understanding of yourself and your chosen field, your life is not dictated by external validation and you are naturally more confident.\n\nI am in no way disputing the efforts that people invest in seeking promotions, I am saying that if we seek mastery as our primary focus - you will be of more value to organisations (and therefore be promoted faster), the people around you and you will live a more enriching life.\n\nI’d love to hear your thoughts on this, do you think promotions enable mastery or vice versa? Share this article to help others join the conversation','{\"tags\":[\"master\",\"success\",\"growth\",\"career\",\"millennial\"],\"app\":\"steemit/0.1\",\"format\":\"markdown\"}','steem','[\"portrayt\",\"babsboard\",\"ramta\",\"barbro\",\"adelja\"]','why-you-should-be-seeking-mastery-and-not-to-be-promoted','SBD','master'),
	(56,'2016-12-14 17:25:51','2016-12-14 17:25:51','outreach','socialmedia','influencers','marketing',226,'hilarski','Why I Believe Influencer Marketing is the Way to Go for Steemit.','37.173 SBD',3,'<center>http://www.200social.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/steemit-outreach-influencers-randy-hilarski.jpg</center>\n\n# Did You Know Influencer Marketing is 11X More Effective Than Banner Ads? #\n\nI have watched as influencer marketing is gaining strength as more and more brands seek out people with influence across social media. It is by far the most effective way for a brand to leverage its ad budget. \n\n<center>http://www.sociableblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/influence-marketing.jpg</center>\n\n *[Source](http://www.sociableblog.com/2016/05/12/power-of-influencer-marketing/)*\n\n## Influencer Marketing is Word of Mouth Advertising in the Digital World. ##\n\nWe all follow people on social media that we respect and listen to their advice. It used to be that we took advice from the local barber, Doctor or our neighbors. Now we trust the advice from people half way across the planet more than our own circles. I know I do! The people I listen to online have gained my trust by continually posting quality content that pertains to the subjects I care about.\n\nBelow are people that are online influencers who have pull in their respective communities online. Steemit does not need a huge ad budget to attract users. These types of users tend to disappear after a short period. When an influencer says something has value, their followers are more likely to come along for the ride.\n\n## Some Examples of Influencers I Trust. ##\n\n### [Chef Dennis Littely](http://www.askchefdennis.com/about-chef-dennis/)- I have known Chef since the early days of Google Plus. He has consistently produced amazing content for his millions of followers across social media.\n\n<center>http://www.askchefdennis.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/dennis-4.jpg</center>\n\n### [Ileane Smith](http://basicblogtips.com/)- Ileane and I have been friends since the early days of Google Plus. She is a social media blogger and Youtube vlogger. Her tips will transform your online presence and her genuine love will touch your soul.\n\n<center>https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/590160440933486593/Ho4Ifdsw_400x400.png</center>\n\n### [Sam Hurley](https://twitter.com/Sam___Hurley)- Top digital marketer and online influencer. Sam rocks it on Twitter and I have been following this power player for years.\n\n<center>https://tttmarketing.files.wordpress.com/2016/07/new-sam-hurley-picture.png?w=748</center>\n\n### [Reginald Chan](https://www.reginaldchan.net/)- Social media and SEO guru. Reginald and I are peers in the social media game. We met through a website called Triberr. I have learned so much from him over the years. \n\n<center>https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/626783665528246274/97RGkTRe_400x400.jpg</center>\n\n### [Dr. Tammy Cashion](http://chirofamilyhealth.com/)- Chiropractor and the epitome of how to be social on social media. Her magic is love and she spreads it across social media far and wide.\n\n<center>https://scontent.fpac1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/14642399_1325868480777040_4669862427124015746_n.jpg?oh=27647ff9186c8b636e51cbf4cb591cdb&oe=58EE4128</center>\n\n### [Amanda Blaine](http://amandablain.com)- Tech lover, Gamer and founder of [Girlfriend Social](http://www.girlfriendsocial.com/). Amanda has spice and a loyal following. We have been online friends since her days of dominating the Google Plus landscape.\n\n<center>http://www.amandablain.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Amanda-new.jpg</center>\n\n### [Alice Beth](https://www.facebook.com/alicebethh)- Alice is a fellow Panama expat who loves the international lifestyle. Her writing is top notch and so inspiring. Her positive energy is infectious!\n\n<center>https://scontent.fpac1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t31.0-8/12747939_10205484583146670_3624096563523270153_o.jpg?oh=d65e38e7e10117933743cac26b2f34e3&oe=58EABD83</center>\n\n### [Ryan Biddulf](https://www.bloggingfromparadise.com)- We met through Triberr when I joined in 2013. He is a master of writing eBooks and supporting his travel around the world through blogging. He is also a guru of staying social on social media.\n\n<center>https://bloggingfromparadise-com.r.worldssl.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/546371_10151048675901674_1203103730_n-e1481483324459.jpg</center>\n\n## Why Steemit Should Choose Influencers Over Any Other Form of Outreach. ##\n\nI am not quiet about my belief that influencer marketing will be the most effective way to attract users to this amazing platform that [Ned](https://steemit.com/@ned), [Dan](https://steemit.com/introduceyourself/@dantheman) and the team have gifted us.\n\nWhen Google Plus launched they effectively leveraged influencers to launch the product. The first two years of Google Plus were some of my best memories on social media. We are now quietly doing the same thing here on [Steemit.com](http://steemit.com) while we work on moving out of Beta.\n\nWhen a group of influencers inform their following about the possibility of earning an income from their content the Steemit platform will explode. We saw what happened when [Jeff Berwick](https://steemit.com/@dollarvigilante) joined. He brought a tidal wave of new users and transformed the Steemit landscape in just a few weeks. We can replicate this across many different topics!\n\nEveryone has a different motivation to see Steemit succeed. Mine is not just the money but a feeling that we are revolutionizing the attention economy. I look forward to attracting the best of the best to evangelize Steemit.\n\n<center>https://img1.steemit.com/0x0/http://www.randyhilarski.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Randy-Banner-Steemit.jpg</center>','{\"tags\":[\"steemit\",\"outreach\",\"socialmedia\",\"influencers\",\"marketing\"],\"image\":[\"http://www.200social.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/steemit-outreach-influencers-randy-hilarski.jpg\",\"http://www.sociableblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/influence-marketing.jpg\",\"http://www.askchefdennis.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/dennis-4.jpg\",\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/590160440933486593/Ho4Ifdsw_400x400.png\",\"https://tttmarketing.files.wordpress.com/2016/07/new-sam-hurley-picture.png?w=748\",\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/626783665528246274/97RGkTRe_400x400.jpg\",\"https://scontent.fpac1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/14642399_1325868480777040_4669862427124015746_n.jpg?oh=27647ff9186c8b636e51cbf4cb591cdb&amp;oe=58EE4128\",\"http://www.amandablain.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Amanda-new.jpg\",\"https://scontent.fpac1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t31.0-8/12747939_10205484583146670_3624096563523270153_o.jpg?oh=d65e38e7e10117933743cac26b2f34e3&amp;oe=58EABD83\",\"https://bloggingfromparadise-com.r.worldssl.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/546371_10151048675901674_1203103730_n-e1481483324459.jpg\",\"https://img1.steemit.com/0x0/http://www.randyhilarski.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Randy-Banner-Steemit.jpg\"],\"links\":[\"http://www.sociableblog.com/2016/05/12/power-of-influencer-marketing/\",\"http://www.askchefdennis.com/about-chef-dennis/\",\"http://basicblogtips.com/\",\"https://twitter.com/Sam___Hurley\",\"https://www.reginaldchan.net/\",\"http://chirofamilyhealth.com/\",\"http://amandablain.com\",\"http://www.girlfriendsocial.com/\",\"https://www.facebook.com/alicebethh\",\"https://www.bloggingfromparadise.com\",\"https://steemit.com/@ned\",\"https://steemit.com/introduceyourself/@dantheman\",\"http://steemit.com\",\"https://steemit.com/@dollarvigilante\"],\"app\":\"steemit/0.1\",\"format\":\"markdown\"}','steem','[\"hilarski\",\"sethlinson\",\"blackmarket\",\"steem-meme\",\"paper-pecado\",\"walhallo777\",\"sunscape\",\"joele\",\"runridefly\",\"anahilarski\",\"steme-meme\",\"djvidov\",\"sergey44\",\"powercouple\",\"teamsteem\",\"jens84\",\"zefa\",\"lamech-m\",\"grandpere\",\"fosho\",\"velourex\",\"slickwilly\",\"kyusho\",\"xer\",\"wang\",\"jocelyn\",\"j