	(65,'2016-12-14 18:08:30','2016-12-14 11:00:00','steemitart','art','steemitartchallenge','[]',0,'steemitart','Introduce: SteemitArt Project','25.640 SBD',0,'We all understand that the key to the existence and development of Steemit is users. Inside the platform created a lot of good communities to maintain the interest of users and their associations, and also to retain them. These communities are doing very useful and important work.\n\nBut, I haven\'t seen projects aimed at attracting new users. It doesn\'t mean that they don\'t exist, I just don\'t know about them.\n\nSo I thought, what can I do for Steemit growth. And I remembered about the category of people, whose work we very often use here, and they are not even aware of the existence of Steemit. **I thought about the artists!**\n\nI\'m talking about creators who work in different areas: painters, photographers, sculptors, makers of installations, graphic designers, cosplayers, writers, poets etc. Already famous or just starting their way to success.\n\n<center>http://i.imgsafe.org/11fc5c7cea.jpg</center>\n\n## <center>The main task of SteemitArt is to attract these amazing people from the outside.</center>\n\nIn each post, I will acquaint you with the work of one artist. After placing the post on Steemit, I will notify the author, that I used his works here. \n\n*Under the comments to the post will be added a screenshot that the author was informed via Facebook, Twitter, Instagram or mail.* After what, I hope, the author may want to join us in the future, he will shares by his works and experience independently.\n\n### All funds raised from the publication of the works, will be immediately transferred to the author, after registration on Steemit.\n (First: because it is honestly. Secondly: it will help to understand to the user that the system of earnings works.)\n\n*It can be assumed that many of them will not have desire to waste their time on Steemit, due to the questionable opportunity to earn on their work. BUT, I believe that the value of this platform is not only money… many will be able to understand it.*\n\n### <center>The second task:</center>\n\nI don\'t want to limit SteemitArt only in one direction. We have a wonderful project ***steemitphotochallenge***, based on this account I would like to create a similar contest #SteemitArtChallenge, in which will be given different tasks and the participants will be rewarded.\n\n*The prize fund will be formed from funds earned from this account. So, I want to contribute to unite the people inside Steemit, for example, as @steemstem.*\n\n****\n\nI often see posts on the topic Steemit vs Facebook, or that Steemit better than other social networks, the meaning of which is opposition and rivalry.  In a sense, this is the wrong approach, it\'s like offering people only a single choice (either you are for us or for them). \n\n**I think that at this stage of development of Steemit we should use the features of other social platforms.**\n\nIt will not a failure If the author, about whom I wrote, will not come to us. Maybe you subscribe to him on Facebook, Twitter or Instagram, and on your page, in turn, already exist or will be mentions of Steemit, Which potentially will become more visible.\n****\n\nI understand that I decided to cover not the largest potential audience, choosing this direction. Still, I very much hope that this project will attract new interesting people and support those, who are already here.\n\n### Waiting for the feedback with your tips and ideas. Thank you for your attention. @steemitart\n\n* *In the next hours I will publish the first post about one author, you will be able to evaluate the principle of operation of the project in practice.* UPD: Done it- <a href=\"https://steemit.com/art/@steemitart/rafael-mantesso-and-jimmy-choo-all-you-need-is-a-wall-marker-and-camera\">Rafael Mantesso and Jimmy Choo</a>\n\n* *In the next two days I will start the first contest.*\n\n### <center>Follow SteemitArt on <a href=\"https://steemit.com/@steemitart\">Steemit</a>, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/steemitart\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100014647051431\">Facebook</a>.</center>','{\"tags\":[\"steemit\",\"steemitart\",\"art\",\"steemitartchallenge\"],\"users\":[\"steemstem\",\"steemitart\"],\"image\":[\"http://i.imgsafe.org/11fc5c7cea.jpg\"],\"links\":[\"https://steemit.com/art/@steemitart/rafael-mantesso-and-jimmy-choo-all-you-need-is-a-wall-marker-and-camera\",\"https://steemit.com/@steemitart\",\"https://twitter.com/steemitart\",\"https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100014647051431\"],\"app\":\"steemit/0.1\",\"format\":\"markdown\"}','steem','[]','introduce-steemitart-project','SBD','steemit'),
