	(106,'2016-12-14 18:00:03','2016-12-14 18:00:03','[]','[]','[]','[]',2,'krasotka','In a Powerful flash of ASASSN-15lh space was the result of a meal of a black hole','0.000 SBD',0,'Astronomers tried to explain the nature of the most powerful of the known outbreaks in space - ASASSN-15lh, which was seen on 14 June 2015\nhttps://kosmos-x.net.ru/_nw/44/81756121.jpg\nStar, torn supermassive black hole. Illustration of ESO, ESA/Hubble, M. Kornmesser\n\nWe will remind that flash of ASASSN-15lh was opened on 14 June 2015 with the assistance system ASAS-SN (All-Sky Automated Survey for Supernovae) is a network of 14 telescopes that are in automatic mode \"combing\" the sky in search of a supernova. Further, the Chinese astronomers observed the event using powerful ground telescopes in order to determine the distance and brightness. The observations were as connected x-ray orbital Observatory \"swift\".\n\nThen the scientists attributed the event to the outbreak hypernovae - the explosion of a massive star whose initial weight ranged from 80 to theoretical limit on the mass of stars in the mass of 150 Suns. The brightness of the flash set twice blocked until a record brightness of supernovae over the entire history of their observations. At the moment of greatest brilliance the object radiated energy, 20 times greater than the entire luminous flux of the milky Way.\n\nScientists estimate that ASASSN-15lh is at a distance of about 4 billion light-years from Earth in the constellation of Indian. Given the distance, it illuminated more than 400 billion times brighter than the Sun, a hundred times brighter than normal supernovae and 2.5 times brighter than any known Hypernova.\n\nHowever, scientists have found a new explanation of the nature of a colossal flare of ASASSN-15lh. In their study, they used data from the surveillance ground-based telescope VLT of the European southern Observatory, New Technology Telescope (NTT) and the space telescope \"Hubble\". As a result, they came to the conclusion that the outbreak of ASASSN-15lh gave rise to black, which literally tore it approached the star.\n\n\"After analyzing the data for the 10 months of observation of the radiation source, we came to the conclusion that he is hardly a flash of bright hypernovae. Our results show that this event is probably associated with a rapidly rotating supermassive black hole that destroyed the star of small mass,\" write the authors of the study.\nhttps://youtu.be/CLqYCO5Cll0\nIn their opinion, the strong gravitational influence of a supermassive black hole located in the center of a distant galaxy, literally \"ripped\" the star about the mass of the Sun, which approached very close to her. The star is literally \"ripped to shreds\", which are coupled in a collision between itself and the heat released in the accretion disk of a black hole, led to a tremendous selection of light energy.\n\nAddress e-links- https://kosmos-x.net.ru/news/moshhnejshaja_vspyshka_v_kosmose_asassn_15lh_stal_rezultatom_trapezy_chernoj_dyry/2016-12-13-4466\nNews about space and UFOs kosmos-x.net.ru © 2009-2016 hosted by uCoz','{\"tags\":[\"life\"],\"image\":[\"https://kosmos-x.net.ru/_nw/44/81756121.jpg\",\"https://img.youtube.com/vi/CLqYCO5Cll0/0.jpg\"],\"links\":[\"https://youtu.be/CLqYCO5Cll0\",\"https://kosmos-x.net.ru/news/moshhnejshaja_vspyshka_v_kosmose_asassn_15lh_stal_rezultatom_trapezy_chernoj_dyry/2016-12-13-4466\"],\"app\":\"steemit/0.1\",\"format\":\"markdown\"}','steem','[\"krasotka\",\"adelja\"]','in-a-powerful-flash-of-asassn-15lh-space-was-the-result-of-a-meal-of-a-black-hole','SBD','life'),
	(107,'2016-12-14 18:17:24','2016-12-14 18:02:27','cinema','war','epic','news',2,'herverisson','Nolan\'s DUNKIRK : First full trailer released','16.387 SBD',0,'<html>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/18c6189088.jpg\" width=\"1288\" height=\"572\"/></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/187ff19ebd.jpg\" width=\"1289\" height=\"571\"/><br>\n</p>\n<p><strong>After a first teaser a few months ago, which was more an appetizer than anything else, Christopher Nolan has released the first full trailer of his upcoming war epic called DUNKIRK. What can we expect of it?&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p>https://youtu.be/XRtZUkAR2u4<br>\n</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>First question is, how do you convert a military disaster into a fully fledge war movie? Usually, Hollywood likes its movies to speak about a great victory, where the victor smashes the hopeless enemy into a thousand little pieces.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/187fa1604b.jpg\" width=\"1291\" height=\"574\"/></p>\n<p>Here, we are 400.000 English (and French) soldiers trapped on the beach of the north of France, by the tanks of the Wehrmacht. It is shown very simply through the propaganda leaflets dropped by the Luftwaffe onto the bemused troops.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/187ff9aec5.jpg\" width=\"1295\" height=\"572\"/></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/187f28c025.jpg\" width=\"1250\" height=\"572\"/></p>\n<p>It is noticeable that the Germans are almost totally absent and invisible from the trailer, except from the occasionnal Stukas dropping bombs and the bullets slashing through the stranded soldiers. The situation is seen first and foremost through the eyes of the soldiers and their chiefs, among which we have Kenneth Branagh of course.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/187fed7ae6.jpg\" width=\"1294\" height=\"573\"/></p>\n<p>The ships of Her Majesty\'s Navy are conspicuous by their absence and when they are, they are easy target for the German planes. The only safe way home will be through the civilians ships who can pick up as many soldiers as possible:</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/1880218ed9.jpg\" width=\"1291\" height=\"576\"/></p>\n<p>And among them, who better than Mark Rylance to embody the typical English pride and guts to face the enemy no matter the cost:</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/187ffbd98f.jpg\" width=\"1272\" height=\"577\"/></p>\n<p>However, the Allies can still rely on their airforce, and this is what will provide the main action sequences and the main thrills of the movie. I didn\'t expect really the movie to cover this side of the conflict, but Nolan seems really decided to provide us with quite a few tight dogfights between Spitfires and Fokkers:</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/187ffccaf7.jpg\" width=\"1289\" height=\"573\"/></p>\n<p>All in all, a spectacular and gripping movie is coming our way.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/187f9311d1.jpg\" width=\"1277\" height=\"573\"/></p>\n<p>A movie which of course has taken another significance due to the extreme upheavals we have experienced in 2016: first, due to the refugee crisis (thousands of people were trapped in the same year for years, trying to reach England and surviving in precarious conditions) and now to Brexit (Britain probably never looked so distant from the continent than during those tense few weeks and days on the shores of France for those lost soldiers desperate to find a way to come back home).</p>\n<h1>Are you looking forward to discovering that movie as much as I am ?</h1>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>\n</html>','{\"tags\":[\"film\",\"cinema\",\"war\",\"art\",\"news\"],\"image\":[\"https://i.imgsafe.org/18c6189088.jpg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/187ff19ebd.jpg\",\"https://img.youtube.com/vi/XRtZUkAR2u4/0.jpg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/187fa1604b.jpg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/187ff9aec5.jpg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/187f28c025.jpg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/187fed7ae6.jpg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/1880218ed9.jpg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/187ffbd98f.jpg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/187ffccaf7.jpg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/187f9311d1.jpg\"],\"links\":[\"https://youtu.be/XRtZUkAR2u4\"],\"app\":\"steemit/0.1\",\"format\":\"html\"}','steem','[\"adelja\",\"zefa\"]','nolan-s-dunkirk-first-full-trailer-released','SBD','film'),
	(108,'2016-12-14 18:03:12','2016-12-14 18:03:12','collaborativeartjourney','photography','poetry','music',13,'everlove','INVITATION:  Collaborative Art Journey...\"Shattered Rainbows\" -- This is your invitation to Collaborate! Whatever your expression, BRING IT ON!',NULL,0,'<html><center>\n<h1>LOOK AT HOW AMAZING WE ARE!! &nbsp;&nbsp;</h1>\n<h3>We are getting to share such personal expression and doing it together at the same time!</h3>\n<h3>This artists\' community is growing stronger with every interaction.</h3>\n<h3>It is truly a blessing to engage our creative spirits and have this incredible portfolio to show for it.</h3>\n<p><br></p>\n<h1>The finale of our most recent collaboration \"<a href=\"https://steemit.com/art/@everlove/finale-all-fired-up-a-collaborative-art-journey-including-17-steemit-artists-and-18-collaborative-masterpieces\">All Fired Up</a>\" included&nbsp;</h1>\n<h1>*** &nbsp;18 artists ***&nbsp;</h1>\n<h1>and &nbsp;</h1>\n<h1>*** 19 collaborative masterpieces! ***&nbsp;</h1>\n<p><strong>Each artist made their own individual post of their finished piece(s) and shared their process. Some artists made more than one and shared those too. &nbsp;</strong><br>\n</p>\n<h1><br>\n&nbsp;NOW is your opportunity to come out and play with us.</h1>\n<h3><strong>&nbsp;~*~*~*~*~ This is the way to play: ~*~*~*~*~</strong></h3>\n<h2><br></h2>\n<h2>1.</h2>\n<h2>I offer up this creation to be used as a base for the collaborative piece.</h2>\n<p><img src=\"https://s6.postimg.org/uqtbw2xbl/69468_1614126840425_6034573_n.jpg\" width=\"640\" height=\"426\"/></p>\n<h6><em>I took this photograph of broken glass that was laying on a sidewalk after the rain. &nbsp;These were colored shards left behind from a broken stained glass window. &nbsp;I was fascinated with the jagged pile of colors and the depths of texture.</em></h6>\n<h2><br></h2>\n<h2>2.</h2>\n<h2>Print the image or do whatever<br>\nit is you need to do to add to/or alter it.<br>\n(i.e., including but not limited to painting, drawing,<br>\nadding other photographs, collaging,<br>\naltering it digitally or however you wish . . .or perhaps even adding a tune, poetry, a story or other imaginative play.</h2>\n<p>You can make as many versions as you\'d like--we wouldn\'t want to stifle ourselves because of number limitations either.</p>\n<h1>We\'re artists, so anything goes!</h1>\n<h2><br></h2>\n<h2>3.<br>\nThen make a post about it,<br>\nsharing your process and anything about it that inspires you.</h2>\n<p>Note: Making a post is not a requirement to play, so don\'t let any time constraints or \"rules\" get your patties up in a wad. &nbsp;But, if you do make a post about it with your process we can share our works more prolifically and people will likely be intrigued by seeing how it developed. &nbsp;I know I will!</p>\n<h2><br></h2>\n<h2>4.<br>\nTag your post with <a href=\"https://steemit.com/trending/art\">#art</a> and <a href=\"https://steemit.com/trending/collaborativeartjourney\">#CollaborativeArtJourney </a>(and of course any other tag that fits your finished piece).</h2>\n<h2><br></h2>\n<h2>5.<br>\nCopy the link from your post into a comment below.</h2>\n<p>(If you don\'t make a post--though I hope you will--please just post your finished piece in the comments below so we can find it easily.)</p>\n<h2><br></h2>\n<h2>6.</h2>\n<h2>Deadline for this submission is<br>\nTuesday, December 20, 2016 at Midnight CST.</h2>\n<h2><strong>After the deadline I will make a post featuring all the collaborations</strong> <strong>and highlighting all the different pieces inspired by the same original photo/art.</strong></h2>\n<p><em>(If you don\'t make it by the deadline, that doesn\'t mean &nbsp;you can\'t play, it just means I may post our finale piece before you get your submission in to be included.)</em></p>\n<h2><br></h2>\n<h2>7.</h2>\n<h2>I will be donating rewards from this post to my favorite and most honorable group doing humanitarian works, @gardenofeden. This week (December 19, 2016) the <a href=\"https://steemit.com/@gardenofeden\">@gardenofeden </a>will <a href=\"https://steemit.com/food/@gardenofeden/did-you-know-it-s-illegal-to-feed-the-homeless-in-dallas-we-do-it-anyway\">procure, prepare and deliver sustainable, hot, home cooked meals to the homeless</a>, and deliver toiletries, tents, blankets, sleeping bags and warm clothing as well.&nbsp;</h2>\n<h3><em>(I am a full-time volunteer at the</em> <a href=\"https://steemit.com/@gardenofeden\"><em>@gardenofeden</em></a><em>, building a new world based on the vision of</em> <a href=\"https://steemit.com/@quinneaker\"><em>@quinneaker</em></a><em>, creating a life based on sustainability, freedom and responsibility--holding space for the betterment of humanity and freedom for the children! &nbsp;This is an incredibly worthy cause I support with 100% of my energy!)</em></h3>\n<h2><br></h2>\n<h2>8.</h2>\n<h2>If you know other artists, musicians, videographers, photographers or others who would also like to play, please share this post so we can get the artistic juices and steem rolling, while expanding our artists\' community for all artists, including others outside the visual arts!</h2>\n<h2><br></h2>\n<h2>9.</h2>\n<h2>Upvote, resteem, share in chats, and make comments to help spread the joy of our artistic endeavors. &nbsp;Supporting each other is truly some of the greatest beauty of this platform. &nbsp;Please take note of other artists\' participation and give them some extra love.</h2>\n<h2><br></h2>\n<h2>10.</h2>\n<h2>IMPORTANT: &nbsp;Soon I will come up with an idea for sharing all of our inspired works. &nbsp;I\'m not sure how that will play out, but please note that by participating in these collaborations, all artists hereby grant permission to have their art shared in &nbsp;some other awesome way (perhaps a show, printing them, making a gift of them, or otherwise). &nbsp;I will give updates as I figure out how best to use them, and of course, give credit where credit is due.If you don\'t want to give permission, please don\'t play.&nbsp;</h2>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>I have a couple of things under consideration for posting and sharing our together art! &nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Keep an eye out for this as starters:<br>\nI am working with the ever bubbly @firepower to put together a chat room where we can display all of our collaborative pieces. &nbsp;That would include all collaborative pieces that anyone works together on, not just those I have instigated. &nbsp;There would be easy access to post and view our repertoire, instead of having to hunt through my posts and others to find them all.  We can also chat about them and spur on the sharing of more collaborative possibilities.</strong></p>\n<h1><br></h1>\n<h1>My day is greatly enhanced by playing with this community. &nbsp;&nbsp;I am <em>overjoyed</em> to received so many ASTOUNDING presents from my Steemian artist friends.\n<P>LET\'S PLAY!!</h1>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br>\n<strong>Get some inspiration for collaboration here:</strong></p>\n<p><em>Most recent collaboration: &nbsp;</em><a href=\"https://steemit.com/art/@everlove/finale-all-fired-up-a-collaborative-art-journey-including-17-steemit-artists-and-18-collaborative-masterpieces\"><em>Finale of All Fired Up</em></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://steemit.com/art/@everlove/collaborative-art-journey-no-strings-attached-this-is-your-invitation-to-collaborate-whatever-your-expression-bring-it-on\"><em>Finale of No Strings Attached</em></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://steemit.com/art/@everlove/artist-s-eye-finale-collaborative-art-journey-look-at-the-beauty-we-created-together\"><em>Finale of Artist\'s Eye</em></a><a href=\"https://steemit.com/art/@everlove/midnight-sky-collaborations-complete-7-collaborating-artists-and-1-unblocked-artist-and-opportunity-still-knocks\"><em>Finale of Midnight Sky</em></a></p>\n<p><em>Zentangle Art</em> <a href=\"https://steemit.com/art/@everlove/who-else-does-this-art-zentangle-style-building-community-together-let-s-collaborate\"><em>Collaboration</em></a></p>\n<p><em>Building community through</em> <a href=\"https://steemit.com/art/@everlove/art-collaboration-building-community-together\"><em>Art Collaboration</em></a></p>\n<p><em>Collaboration using</em> <a href=\"https://steemit.com/art/@merej99/calling-all-artists-illustrators-animators-musicians-and-videographers-how-about-a-sitewide-collaboration-using-ned-s-head-let-s\"><em>Ned\'s Head</em></a></p>\n<p><em>Completed collaboration with</em> <a href=\"https://steemit.com/@opheliafu\"><em>@opheliafu</em></a><em>: &nbsp;</em><a href=\"https://steemit.com/art/@everlove/i-get-to-do-art-with-opheliafu-collaborative-treasures\"><em>Madam Kali</em> </a><em>and</em> <a href=\"https://steemit.com/collaborativeartjourney/@everlove/collaboration-in-the-arts-playing-games-with-opheliafu-do-you-want-to-play-too\"><em>Bird on a Wing</em></a><br>\n</p>\n</center></html>','{\"tags\":[\"art\",\"collaborativeartjourney\",\"photography\",\"poetry\",\"music\"],\"users\":[\"gardenofeden\",\"quinneaker\",\"firepower\",\"opheliafu\"],\"image\":[\"https://s6.postimg.org/uqtbw2xbl/69468_1614126840425_6034573_n.jpg\"],\"links\":[\"https://steemit.com/art/@everlove/finale-all-fired-up-a-collaborative-art-journey-including-17-steemit-artists-and-18-collaborative-masterpieces\",\"https://steemit.com/trending/art\",\"https://steemit.com/trending/collaborativeartjourney\",\"https://steemit.com/@gardenofeden\",\"https://steemit.com/food/@gardenofeden/did-you-know-it-s-illegal-to-feed-the-homeless-in-dallas-we-do-it-anyway\",\"https://steemit.com/@quinneaker\",\"https://steemit.com/art/@everlove/collaborative-art-journey-no-strings-attached-this-is-your-invitation-to-collaborate-whatever-your-expression-bring-it-on\",\"https://steemit.com/art/@everlove/artist-s-eye-finale-collaborative-art-journey-look-at-the-beauty-we-created-together\",\"https://steemit.com/art/@everlove/midnight-sky-collaborations-complete-7-collaborating-artists-and-1-unblocked-artist-and-opportunity-still-knocks\",\"https://steemit.com/art/@everlove/who-else-does-this-art-zentangle-style-building-community-together-let-s-collaborate\",\"https://steemit.com/art/@everlove/art-collaboration-building-community-together\",\"https://steemit.com/art/@merej99/calling-all-artists-illustrators-animators-musicians-and-videographers-how-about-a-sitewide-collaboration-using-ned-s-head-let-s\",\"https://steemit.com/@opheliafu\",\"https://steemit.com/art/@everlove/i-get-to-do-art-with-opheliafu-collaborative-treasures\",\"https://steemit.com/collaborativeartjourney/@everlove/collaboration-in-the-arts-playing-games-with-opheliafu-do-you-want-to-play-too\"],\"app\":\"steemit/0.1\",\"format\":\"html\"}','steem','[\"everlove\",\"soyjoseluis\",\"adelja\",\"saramiller\",\"gardenofeden\",\"quinneaker\",\"summonerrk\",\"mmcrae\",\"awesomenyl\",\"batanamatampuhin\",\"diyfun\",\"mindfreak\",\"meesterboom\"]','invitation-collaborative-art-journey-shattered-rainbows-this-is-your-invitation-to-collaborate-whatever-your-expression-bring-it','SBD','art'),
	(109,'2016-12-14 18:05:09','2016-12-14 18:05:09','philosophy','howto','health','mindfulness',1,'jg02','Be Grateful for Challenges','2.429 SBD',0,'**If everything in life had gone as I hoped, I would be miserable.**  The same is true for you. It is only through adversity that we grow into who we are meant to be.\n\nThink about a challenge you faced and how you were forced to respond to it.  How did you change in response? Are you more resilient now to future challenges?  What things in your life do you have now that wouldn’t exist if you had always gotten your way?  Have you met people who have everything handed to them in life? Do you want to be like those people?\n\nI suspect that in answering the above questions, you will come to a similar conclusion as I did. **It was only through my desires getting frustrated that I have been able to grow into the person I am today and to accomplish what I have accomplished.**  I will share a few of those stories to illustrate.\n\n\n# Debate Magic\nhttps://d2mxuefqeaa7sj.cloudfront.net/s_1FEA94F7903AF678C113DA704096D8BF9309AF04C6B64B433395D3AEEC749FD6_1481737346218_exchange-of-ideas-222790_1920.jpg\n\n\nI loved high school debate tournaments.  In order to compete at a national level, I wanted to go to debate camp for the summer.  My family couldn’t afford to send me, and I was crushed. My debate career was over.  \n\nThat same summer, I played a game called Magic, the Gathering, and qualified for the national championship event (but still couldn’t afford to go). This time I wouldn’t let money stop me.   I ran a tournament at the local game store to pay for my plane ticket.  I slept on a friend’s hotel room floor at the event. I won the tournament and became the US National Champion, leading to a career as a professional Magic player that helped pay my way through college. \n\n**If not for the failure to get what I wanted, I would never have the life I love today.**\n\n\n# Law Fool\nhttps://d2mxuefqeaa7sj.cloudfront.net/s_1FEA94F7903AF678C113DA704096D8BF9309AF04C6B64B433395D3AEEC749FD6_1481737619516_library-869061_1920.jpg\n\n\nSince I was a little boy, I was destined to become a lawyer.  Both my parents are lawyers.  I continued to debate throughout high school and college.  In high school I was voted “Most likely to disagree with anything you say.” I taught courses on how to ace the LSAT (law school admission test). I was accepted to one of the top 5 law schools in the country, and realized I was miserable. \n\nAs much as I liked debating philosophy and world politics, I hated the minutiae of the law, poring over contracts, and the day to day adversarial lifestyle. \n\nWhen I told my mom I was dropping out of law school, she cried.  It was difficult to follow an unconventional path, but this opened the door to my career as a game designer. Eventually, I starting my own company and am now happier than I’ve ever been.\n\n\n# Love Actually\nhttps://d2mxuefqeaa7sj.cloudfront.net/s_1FEA94F7903AF678C113DA704096D8BF9309AF04C6B64B433395D3AEEC749FD6_1481737846860_broken-1739128_1920.jpg\n\n\nThe single most painful event in my life was my divorce.  I had been with my then wife since freshman year of college (almost 12 years). When my marriage fell apart, I was devastated.  I would not wish that experience on my worst enemy.  \n\nBut slowly, over the years, two things happened:\n\nFirst, I poured my energy into starting my company, spending countless hours to help it grow and develop.  The work helped me forget the pain for a time, and led to the successful launch of our first game, [Ascension](http://www.ascensiongame.com).  That foundation of hard work has allowed me to continue to grow and support my business to this day.\n\nSecond, and more importantly, **my divorce forced me to take a hard look at myself in relationship.**  I realized things about myself I never wanted to see and have spent years working to become a better person both for myself and for the loved ones in my life.  **Without the pain of loss, I would never have taken the difficult steps to become a person who deserves the love I want.**\n\n# Every Challenge is an Opportunity\nhttps://d2mxuefqeaa7sj.cloudfront.net/s_1FEA94F7903AF678C113DA704096D8BF9309AF04C6B64B433395D3AEEC749FD6_1481738161124_achieve-1822503_1280.jpg\n\n\nToday, I am in a wonderful relationship, a thriving business, and feel more capable of dealing with loss because of the challenges I’ve faced.  \n\nI still face challenges that scare me. I suspect the same is true for you reading this right now.  This article is here to give us both the strength to face these challenges.  **Reframe each challenge as an opportunity and accept that what you think you want may not be what you really need**.\n\nIt won’t be pleasant, but **if you face difficulties with an open mind, a willingness to learn, and the ability to pick yourself up after you fall down, then challenges are the best thing that can happen to you.**','{\"tags\":[\"life\",\"philosophy\",\"howto\",\"health\",\"mindfulness\"],\"image\":[\"https://d2mxuefqeaa7sj.cloudfront.net/s_1FEA94F7903AF678C113DA704096D8BF9309AF04C6B64B433395D3AEEC749FD6_1481737346218_exchange-of-ideas-222790_1920.jpg\",\"https://d2mxuefqeaa7sj.cloudfront.net/s_1FEA94F7903AF678C113DA704096D8BF9309AF04C6B64B433395D3AEEC749FD6_1481737619516_library-869061_1920.jpg\",\"https://d2mxuefqeaa7sj.cloudfront.net/s_1FEA94F7903AF678C113DA704096D8BF9309AF04C6B64B433395D3AEEC749FD6_1481737846860_broken-1739128_1920.jpg\",\"https://d2mxuefqeaa7sj.cloudfront.net/s_1FEA94F7903AF678C113DA704096D8BF9309AF04C6B64B433395D3AEEC749FD6_1481738161124_achieve-1822503_1280.jpg\"],\"links\":[\"http://www.ascensiongame.com\"],\"app\":\"steemit/0.1\",\"format\":\"markdown\"}','steem','[\"jg02\"]','be-grateful-for-challenges','SBD','life'),
	(110,'2016-12-14 18:05:09','2016-12-14 14:11:48','steemitart','photography','[]','[]',0,'steemitart','Rafael Mantesso and Jimmy Choo: All you need is a wall, marker and camera','0.194 SBD',0,'Our first \"guest\" is already famous enough. Allow me to introduce: Rafael Mantesso (photographer and artist from Brazil) and his bull terrier Jimmy Choo, together they create the amazing works. \n\n<center>http://i.imgsafe.org/14f0fe4454.jpg</center>\n\nJimmy posing on a white background, and Rafael draws the environment, creating short adventure stories.\n<center>http://i.imgsafe.org/14f0f2be4a.jpg</center>\n\nAccording to Rafael, the idea came to him in an unexpected moment:\n>On my thirtieth birthday, my wife left me. She took her cookware, furniture, photos, her decorations. She left me alone in an empty all-white apartment. The only thing she didn’t take was my bull terrier, whom she’d named after her favorite shoe designer: Jimmy Choo. With only Jimmy for company, I found inspiration in my blank walls and my best friend and started snapping photos of Jimmy Choo as he trotted and cavorted around the house in glee. When Jimmy collapsed in happy exhaustion next to the white wall, I grabbed a marker and drew a new world around his ginger-eared pup. Suddenly, I felt his long-dormant inspiration for drawing, for art, for life—returning\n\n<center>http://i.imgsafe.org/14f0c0b412.png</center>\n\n>I created a series of fun, tongue-in-cheek illustrations, portraying my bull terrier dreaming of shoes, relaxing on a sofa with a martini by his side or turning canine DJ on the decks. Set against a matte white background, the illustrations are humorous and eye-catching juxtaposed with bright pops of iridescent color in hot pink, copper and electric blue. I added the best pictures of Jimmy to one book, which is coming on October. ***<a href=\"http://www.boredpanda.com/interactive-illustrations-bull-terrier-jimmy-choo-rafael-mantesso/\">source</a>***\n\nToday created a few hundred photos with different subjects. Jimmy and Rafael have thousands of fans, already formed own brand, which is very popular. Jimmy Choo became the face of a video campaign of accessories collection from the same name designer. Was released book with the works of Raphael. On instagram he has over 600 thousand subscribers.\n\n<center>http://i.imgsafe.org/14fe7392a0.jpg</center>\n\nA great example of how the exit from comfort zone (though forced) helps to find inspiration, where it was not visible before.\n\n### <center>**You can thoroughly get acquainted with their creativity here: <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/rafaelmantesso/\">Instagram</a>, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/jimmythebull_\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/JimmyTheBullTerrier/\">Facebook</a>, <a href=\"http://jimmythebull.com/about\">jimmythebull.com</a>**</center>\n<center>*all images in this post obtained from public sources.*</center>\n### <center>***</center>\n\nOf course, I understand that Rafael may be too busy  to respond to this post. But, that is not a reason not to introduce you to his wonderful works. *And to demonstrate the principle of operation of the project <a href=\"https://steemit.com/steemit/@steemitart/introduce-steemitart-project\">SteemitArt.</a>*\n\n* All funds raised from the publication of these works, will be immediately transferred to the author, after registration on Steemit.\n* Otherwise, funds will be directed to the creation of the prize pool for future contests of SteemitArt project.\n* Under the comments to the post will be added a screenshot that the author was informed via Facebook, Twitter, Instagram or mail.\n\n### <center>Follow SteemitArt on <a href=\"https://steemit.com/@steemitart\">Steemit</a>, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/steemitart\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100014647051431\">Facebook</a>.</center>','{\"tags\":[\"art\",\"steemitart\",\"photography\"],\"image\":[\"http://i.imgsafe.org/14f0fe4454.jpg\",\"http://i.imgsafe.org/14f0f2be4a.jpg\",\"http://i.imgsafe.org/14f0c0b412.png\",\"http://i.imgsafe.org/14fe7392a0.jpg\"],\"links\":[\"http://www.boredpanda.com/interactive-illustrations-bull-terrier-jimmy-choo-rafael-mantesso/\",\"https://www.instagram.com/rafaelmantesso/\",\"https://twitter.com/jimmythebull_\",\"https://www.facebook.com/JimmyTheBullTerrier/\",\"http://jimmythebull.com/about\",\"https://steemit.com/steemit/@steemitart/introduce-steemitart-project\",\"https://steemit.com/@steemitart\",\"https://twitter.com/steemitart\",\"https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100014647051431\"],\"app\":\"steemit/0.1\",\"format\":\"markdown\"}','steem','[]','rafael-mantesso-and-jimmy-choo-all-you-need-is-a-wall-marker-and-camera','SBD','art'),
