	(150,'2016-12-15 10:26:18','2016-12-15 09:53:21','life','blog','nature','[]',1,'konstantin','The Indians found in the woods the sorting hat','0.758 SBD',0,'<html>\n<p>http://tinyimg.io/i/uovLhgT.jpg</p>\n<h3>Indian arachnologists has found a spider similar to a hat, in the South-West of India. New species was given the name Eriovixia gryffindori in honor of the sorting hat belonged to Godric Gryffindor house, the character of a series of books by JK Rowling about Harry Potter.</h3>\n<h3>According to scientists, perpetuating a Hat in the name of the spider, they tried to draw attention to the \"charming but neglected by the world of invertebrates and their secret life\".</h3>\n<h3>The spider belongs to the genus Eriovixia, the representatives of which, according to scientists, possess the ability to pretend dry leaves. In this they are similar to spiders of another kind of the same family of Orb-web spiders, which appearance similar to the leaves not only color and shape, and \"veins\".</h3>\n<h3>New species <a href=\"chrome-extension://ilhapdfjlmhfdgdbefpinebijmhjijpn/http://indianarachnology.com/ija/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/ija_2016_v5_n1_2_p7_24_27.pdf\">described</a> in the journal Indian Journal of Arachnology.</h3>\n<p>Indian Journal of Arachnology &nbsp;</p>\n<p>http://chrdk.ru/images/logotip.png</p>\n</html>','{\"tags\":[\"science\",\"life\",\"blog\",\"nature\"],\"image\":[\"http://tinyimg.io/i/uovLhgT.jpg\",\"http://chrdk.ru/images/logotip.png\"],\"links\":[\"chrome-extension://ilhapdfjlmhfdgdbefpinebijmhjijpn/http://indianarachnology.com/ija/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/ija_2016_v5_n1_2_p7_24_27.pdf\"],\"app\":\"steemit/0.1\",\"format\":\"html\"}','steem','[\"konstantin\"]','the-indians-found-in-the-woods-the-sorting-hat','SBD','science'),
	(151,'2016-12-15 10:14:45','2016-12-15 09:55:54','photography','christmas','recipe','[]',66,'gringalicious','? DARK CHOCOLATE & CRANBERRY with PISTACHIO GRANOLA - Edible Gift Ideas ? FOOD PHOTO SHOOT & RECIPE ?','14.177 SBD',0,'<center><h3>*It\'s Thursday the 15th!  10 Days People, only 10 days until Christmas!!*</h3></center>\n\n<center>https://s19.postimg.org/50gcalz3n/Edible_Gifting_Week_4_Dark_Chocolate_Cranberry_P.jpg</center>\n\n<center>Do you have all your gifts in place?  How about some edible gifts?</center>\n\n<center>https://s19.postimg.org/bs6rdgo37/Edible_Gifting_Week_4_Dark_Chocolate_Cranberry_P.jpg</center>\n\n<center>Edible gifts by your own creation will say a lot.  They\'ll remember you and the gift for a long time to come.</center>\n\n<center>https://s19.postimg.org/f0b8qiacz/Edible_Gifting_Week_4_Dark_Chocolate_Cranberry_P.jpg</center>\n\nIn case you missed it, here are some of my other edible gift ideas:\n\n1.  [HOMEMADE SPICE MIXES](https://steemit.com/food/@gringalicious/edible-gift-giving-ideas-homemade-spice-mixes-5-mix-recipes-included-food-photo-shoot) - Put your own twist to ready made spice mixes. Who knows, maybe you\'ll start your owne brand?\n2.  [CHOCOLATE DIPPED SALTED CARAMELS](https://steemit.com/food/@gringalicious/chocolate-dipped-salted-caramels-corn-syrup-free-edible-gift-giving-no-2-food-photo-shoot) - Do I really need to say more?\n3.  [CHOCOLATE BLACK SESAME PEANUT BUTTER TRUFFLES](https://steemit.com/food/@gringalicious/chocolate-dipped-salted-caramels-corn-syrup-free-edible-gift-giving-no-2-food-photo-shoot) - Yup, more chocolate, how can you go wrong?\n4.  [WHITE CHOCOLATE GINGERBREAD FUDGE](https://steemit.com/food/@gringalicious/white-chocolate-gingerbread-fudge-edible-gift-giving-ideas-food-photo-shoot)\n\n<center>https://s19.postimg.org/yw7861reb/Edible_Gifting_Week_4_Dark_Chocolate_Cranberry_P.jpg</center>\n\nI do not know about you, but I just can\'t believe how fast this month is going.  The 14th, it just doesn\'t seem possible.\n\n<center>https://s19.postimg.org/edcc0zdgz/Edible_Gifting_Week_4_Dark_Chocolate_Cranberry_P.jpg</center>\n\nNot only is my house busy with all things Christmas, but the town we live in is a buzz also.  Our town is a tourist town and tourist season is in high gear.  People from all over Europe are here as well as some from the states.\n\n<center>https://s19.postimg.org/f4526rfub/Edible_Gifting_Week_4_Dark_Chocolate_Cranberry_P.jpg</center>\n\nWell, this is one of my granola recipes and it is always a hit.  I know it would be a great gift for your friends and family.\n\n<center>https://s19.postimg.org/j1sbw62nn/Edible_Gifting_Week_4_Dark_Chocolate_Cranberry_P.jpg</center>\n\nOn a side note:  I enjoy doing these side notes near the end of the post.  This is where I can find out who actually read my posts.  I realize everyone is super busy, I totally get it, I don\'t take offense.  The note I wanted to make is this - I have known this for a long time, but the point was driven hard home the past two days.  Hard work, quality posts, high reputations score, a large number of followers, a large amount of steempower, .... none of it means anything to a post unless a whales comes by and gives a little wink.  I had three posts, by my standards very good posts, totally flop, I mean like I want to take all my toys and go home flop.  So, I just have to shake it off and keep Steeming On!\n\n<center>https://s19.postimg.org/fw7q5yk1f/Edible_Gifting_Week_4_Dark_Chocolate_Cranberry_P.jpg</center>\n\n<h1><center>RECIPE</h1></center>\n\n<h3>Ingredients</h3>\n\n1/2 cup honey\n1/4 cup sunflower oil\n1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon\n1 teaspoon salt\nzest from 1 orange\n1/2 teaspoons vanilla\n3 cups old-fashioned oats\n1/2 cup unsweetened, dried coconut flakes\n1/4 cup pepitas\n1/2 cup shelled pistachios, roughly chopped\n2/3 cup dried cranberries\n1/2 cup semi-sweet dark chocolate chips or chunks\n\n<h3>Instructions</h3>\n\n1.  Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (180 C). Combine honey, oil, salt, and cinnamon in a medium saucepan and place over low heat. Stir for about 3 minutes until warm. Renove from heat and add vanilla and zest, then stir until smooth. Add oats and coconut and stir to combine.\n2.  Spread out granola on a parchment lined baking sheet and bake for about 10 minutes. then remove from oven and stir in pepitas and pistachios with spatula. Return to oven and bake for 10 to 12 minutes longer until crisp. Remove from oven and cool completely.\n3.  Once cooled, add craisins and chocolate and pour into a jar or container with lid. Should keep at room temp for at least 2 weeks.\n\n<center>https://s19.postimg.org/wy0k81ywj/Edible_Gifting_Week_4_Dark_Chocolate_Cranberry_P.jpg</center>\n\nALL CONTENT IS MINE AND ORIGINAL! All of these food photos were taken with my Nikon D5300 and my favorite Lens, the Nikon AF-S FX NIKKOR 50mm f/1.8G. You can find out more in my [INTRO POST.](https://steemit.com/introduceyourself/@gringalicious/hola-steemit-photographer-food-blogger-traveler-and-student-of-life-i-am)\n\n\n<center>https://s19.postimg.org/ewm0nzu9f/Edible_Gifting_Week_4_Dark_Chocolate_Cranberry_P.jpg</center>\n\n<center>https://s19.postimg.org/vkm26hwtv/allpurpose_COLL203.jpg</center>\n<br>\n<center><img src=\"https://s19.postimg.org/674875l6b/Gringalicious_Headerlast.jpg\" width=\"1200\" height=\"510\"/></center>\n<p><center><strong>AND A HUGE MASSIVE SHOUT OUT TO</strong><a href=\"https://steemit.com/@rigaronib\"><strong>@rigaronib</strong></a> <strong>for designing my logo!!!!</center></strong>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n<center>I am always open to feedback, and would love to know how you feel I could do better and please do not forget to </center></p><p><h1><center>UPVOTE AND FOLLOW ME</h1></center></p><p>\n<p><center><img src=\"https://s19.postimg.org/shykdwg37/gringalicious.png\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\"/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<img src=\"https://s19.postimg.org/dfq8tupkj/n_ORxwdg_200.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"182\"/>https