	(169,'2016-12-15 15:48:42','2016-12-15 15:48:42','christmas','howto','diy','lifestyle',3,'yogidream.scapes','Easy Christmas Cupcakes - Icing Ideas (without fondant)','0.710 SBD',0,'<html>\n<h1><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b06b613d2.jpg\" width=\"1440\" height=\"1080\"/></h1>\n<h1>Hi Everyone!</h1>\n<p>Today I was feeling especially festive, and decided to bake some cupcakes for my loved ones. In the town I live in, one of the things I am best known for is these cupcakes. They are absolutely delicious, and so easy to make.</p>\n<p><strong>Here is the recipe I use for the cupcakes,</strong></p>\n<p>http://www.food.com/recipe/simple-vanilla-cupcakes-178370</p>\n<p>But when I make them, I add a little more vanilla, and (what I think helps the most) I vary the amount of milk depending on the weather. If it is a very hot or dry day, I add a bit more milk than the recipe states. If it is a humid or rainy day, I keep the amount the same.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b074a2d70.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\"/></p>\n<p><strong>For the icing, I don\'t use an exact recipe, but here\'s what I do.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>I take some butter(amounts vary depending on how much I\'m making) and about double the amount in icing sugar. I use an electric beater to mix them together until combined.&nbsp;</li>\n  <li>Next I add some milk, and icing sugar, alternating until it reaches a thick but fluffy consistency.</li>\n  <li>You can adapt this however you want. If you want it more runny, add more milk. If you want it stiffer, add more icing sugar.</li>\n  <li>&nbsp;Lastly, add some vanilla essence. This gives it a lovely taste.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you want a more exact recipe, here is one you can use.</p>\n<p>http://www.bettycrocker.com/recipes/vanilla-buttercream-frosting/39107a19-be94-4571-9031-f1fc5bd1d606</p>\n<p>The icing ideas I have compiled are easy, and more abstract looking, which is good for us non-professionals. It is less easy to mess up something that is free form, and I like ( cough, need) that.</p>\n<p><strong>Let\'s Begin!</strong></p>\n<p>Take your frosting and separate it into 3 bowls.<img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b10a84c95.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\"/></p>\n<p>Add some red food colouring to one bowl, green to another, and leave the rest white.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b10f469e0.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\"/></p>\n<h2><strong>Design #1:</strong></h2>\n<p><strong>* Cute Christmas Tree</strong></p>\n<p>Note: Before beginning, make sure the cupcakes are thoroughly cooled, and the frosting is not too runny.</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Put the mint green frosting into a piping bag with a star-tipped nozzle.</li>\n  <li>Pipe the icing onto the cupcake, by making a circle and layering it like a tree. Each circle smaller than the last.</li>\n  <li>Put some of the white frosting into a piping bag with a small rounded nozzle. make a big dot on top of the tree.</li>\n  <li>Put some of the red frosting into a piping bag with a small rounded nozzle as well, and make small dots all over the tree with the red and white.</li>\n  <li>You could also use round candies, depending on the size and look.</li>\n  <li>Finish it off with a light dusting of gold edible glitter.(optional)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b19196dc1.jpeg\" width=\"1059\" height=\"1080\"/></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b1792180b.jpeg\" width=\"919\" height=\"1080\"/></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b183c861a.jpeg\" width=\"837\" height=\"1080\"/></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b1824ccdf.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"789\"/></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b18808f98.jpeg\" width=\"608\" height=\"1080\"/></p>\n<p><strong>* Simple Wreath</strong></p>\n<p>Note: All of the same piping bags and frosting are used for all of the designs.</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Ice the top of the cupcake with white frosting. Smooth it out with a butter knife.</li>\n  <li>Take the green frosting bag and pipe dots in a circle. The star tip will make the dots look like stars. A tip for doing this, would be to hold the bag steadily up against the cupcake, apply a small amount of pressure for a few seconds, and then quickly lift the bag up.&nbsp;</li>\n  <li>Use the red bag to pipe small dots all over the circle.&nbsp;</li>\n  <li>At the top, add a bow by simply making two oval shaped loops, touching at the base and leaning to an angle (almost like an eight). Where the two bases meet pipe two wavy lines.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b19196dc1.jpeg\" width=\"1059\" height=\"1080\"/></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b2a734c8b.jpeg\" width=\"913\" height=\"1080\"/></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b2acd72cb.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"989\"/></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b2b634121.jpeg\" width=\"1115\" height=\"1080\"/></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b2b9ebf07.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"915\"/><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b2aa4e59d.jpeg\" width=\"1067\" height=\"1080\"/></p>\n<p><strong>* Snowflake&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p>Note: If you do not have edible glitter, add a TINY amount of light blue food colouring to the white frosting before applying it to the cupcake. This will help the snowflake stand out.</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Ice the top of the cupcake in white (or light blue) frosting and smooth it out.</li>\n  <li>Put some light blue edible glitter over the top to make it look like snow.</li>\n  <li>Using the white piping bag (still with the small round nozzle), pipe a rough star in the middle. Pipe base lines coming off of the star, and then lines coming off of the base lines as shown below. It really doesn\'t have to be perfect. They also get better with practice as I noticed.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b19196dc1.jpeg\" width=\"1059\" height=\"1080\"/></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b2a734c8b.jpeg\" width=\"913\" height=\"1080\"/></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b43bb91bf.jpeg\" width=\"837\" height=\"1080\"/></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b4327296a.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\"/></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b4532eef5.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\"/></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b43bd03d4.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\"/></p>\n<p><strong>* Coconut Holly Berry</strong></p>\n<p>I made these especially for my dad, they are reminiscent of a cake my &nbsp;Grand-mère used to make with coconut and apricot jam.</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Hollow out the middle of the cupcake and add a little bit of apricot jam. place the crumbs on top to fill the hole.&nbsp;</li>\n  <li>Ice the top of the cupcake with white frosting and smooth it out. It\'s alright if it\'s not perfect.</li>\n  <li>Cover the top of the cupcake with desiccated coconut to look like snow.</li>\n  <li>Using the red frosting bag, pipe three large-ish dots in a triangular shape.&nbsp;</li>\n  <li>Pipe leaf-like shapes on either side of the triangle.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b19196dc1.jpeg\" width=\"1059\" height=\"1080\"/></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b4f85e8e8.jpeg\" width=\"979\" height=\"1080\"/></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b50d406cf.jpeg\" width=\"1211\" height=\"1080\"/></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b50b1ed1d.jpeg\" width=\"1253\" height=\"1080\"/></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b50b71527.jpeg\" width=\"835\" height=\"1080\"/></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b557903cf.jpeg\" width=\"608\" height=\"1080\"/></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b55ae684a.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\"/></p>\n<p>And there you have it, four cute and simple designs you can use for any Christmas party.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b71d12655.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"1022\"/></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b71f3ddcd.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\"/></p>\n<p>I found these cute foil things that you can put the cupcakes in, which makes them look a lot fancier, so that\'s an easy way to glam up simple cupcakes too.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b72b9f7df.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\"/></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b72dd8780.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"720\"/></p>\n<p>I hope you liked this, let me know in the comments if you have any questions or if you are going to try it.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Have a lovely day everyone!</p>\n<p><em>Photos taken by me, (@thatguyjono was too busy trying to eat everything.)</em></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b727359b4.jpeg\" width=\"608\" height=\"1080\"/></p>\n<p>Namaste</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b72757ae9.jpeg\" width=\"1440\" height=\"1080\"/></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><br></p>\n</html>','{\"tags\":[\"food\",\"christmas\",\"howto\",\"diy\",\"lifestyle\"],\"image\":[\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b06b613d2.jpg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b074a2d70.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b10a84c95.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b10f469e0.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b19196dc1.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b1792180b.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b183c861a.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b1824ccdf.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b18808f98.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b2a734c8b.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b2acd72cb.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b2b634121.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b2b9ebf07.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b2aa4e59d.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b43bb91bf.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b4327296a.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b4532eef5.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b43bd03d4.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b4f85e8e8.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b50d406cf.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b50b1ed1d.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b50b71527.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b557903cf.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b55ae684a.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b71d12655.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b71f3ddcd.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b72b9f7df.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b72dd8780.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b727359b4.jpeg\",\"https://i.imgsafe.org/2b72757ae9.jpeg\"],\"links\":[\"http://www.food.com/recipe/simple-vanilla-cupcakes-178370\",\"http://www.bettycrocker.com/recipes/vanilla-buttercream-frosting/39107a19-be94-4571-9031-f1fc5bd1d606\"],\"app\":\"steemit/0.1\",\"format\":\"html\"}','steem','[\"yogidream.scapes\",\"f1111111\",\"adelja\"]','easy-christmas-cupcakes-icing-ideas-without-fondant','SBD','food'),
