	(172,'2016-12-15 15:46:45','2016-12-15 15:46:45','cats','[]','[]','[]',4,'whatageek','TIL Why Your Cat Will Risk Harm Just To Get To A Laser Pointer',NULL,0,'<html>\n<p>Must. Get. Dot. Either you have done it or you have seen a video of it. When someone shines a laser pointer light in front of a cat, the cat goes berserk trying to capture that red dot, like a pac-man on drugs. So why is that so? Appearently it comes down to the fact that cats can\'t make out the colour red and this leads the cat to think the dot is prey. To the cat eyes, the dot appears yellow or white. And cats being predators, when they see something they can stalk and bounce, they get right on it.</p>\n<p>Here is the full article for me details:</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://now.howstuffworks.com/2016/12/13/cats-laser-pointers\">http://now.howstuffworks.com/2016/12/13/cats-laser-pointers&nbsp;</a></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://s29.postimg.org/4wd6g3lpz/laser_160991_1280.png\" width=\"1280\" height=\"640\"/></p>\n</html>','{\"tags\":[\"til\",\"cats\"],\"image\":[\"https://s29.postimg.org/4wd6g3lpz/laser_160991_1280.png\"],\"links\":[\"http://now.howstuffworks.com/2016/12/13/cats-laser-pointers\"],\"app\":\"steemit/0.1\",\"format\":\"html\"}','steem','[\"whatageek\",\"f1111111\",\"adelja\",\"karenmckersie\"]','til-why-your-cat-will-risk-harm-just-to-get-to-a-laser-pointer','SBD','til'),
